1. Title Slide — RHEL Shortcuts, Tips, and Tricks

“Today I’m going to walk through some RHEL shortcuts, tips, and tricks that can make command-line work faster, cleaner, and safer.

This is not meant to be a deep dive into every Linux command. The goal is to show practical habits that help with real tasks like checking services, reviewing logs, moving around the filesystem, and troubleshooting under pressure.”

