2. Purpose

“The purpose of this session is to help newer team members get more comfortable and efficient on the RHEL command line.

A lot of these commands are small, but they save time because they reduce repetitive typing, help avoid mistakes, and give us a more repeatable way to troubleshoot.

The goal is for this to feel useful right away, not like a random list of commands to memorize.”

