“These shortcuts fit into the kind of work we already do.

When we’re checking service health, reviewing logs, troubleshooting connectivity, checking firewall rules, SELinux, ports, permissions, or disk space, the command line is usually part of the process.

These commands do not replace approved runbooks or team procedures. They help us move through those procedures faster and more consistently.”

