20. Vim Survival and vimtutor

“Vim can be intimidating if you do not use it often, but on RHEL it is useful to know enough to survive.

You do not need to be a Vim expert. The basics are: enter insert mode, leave insert mode, search, save, and quit.”

Demo line:
“I’ll run vimtutor just to show that it exists. It is a safe interactive lesson for learning Vim. Then I’ll open a demo config file, use :set number, search with /port, and quit with :q!.”

Transition:
“The main thing is: if Vim opens, do not panic. Press Esc, then use :q! if you need to leave without saving.”

