22. Shell Expansion Tricks

“Shell expansion lets Bash do repetitive typing for us.

Brace expansion can create several directories or files at once. Command substitution lets us put the output of one command inside another command, which is great for dated backup names.”

Demo line:
“I’ll run mkdir -p project/{bin,etc,logs,tmp} and show the result with tree. Then I’ll use cp app.conf{,.bak} to quickly make a backup. Finally, I’ll create a directory named backup-$(date +%F).”

Transition:
“These tricks make names more consistent and reduce repetitive typing.”

