37. Disk and Filesystem Checks

“This slide is a disk-space triage flow.

df -hT tells us filesystem usage and type. du -sh helps us drill into what is using space. lsblk, findmnt, and mount help us understand devices and mounts.”

Demo line:
“I’ll start with df -hT to see filesystem usage. Then I’ll use du -sh /tmp/rhel-demo/* | sort -h to see what is taking space in the demo directory.”

Transition:
“The cool trick here is lsof +L1, which can show deleted files that are still held open by a process.”

⸻

38. Networking Quick Checks

“This slide is about checking the basics: IP address, route, listening ports, DNS, and connectivity.

ip -br addr gives a clean address view. ip route shows routing. ss -tulpen shows listening ports and connections. getent hosts checks name resolution.”

Demo line:
“I’ll run ip -br addr, then ip route, then ss -tulpen. If I’m checking SSH, I can grep for port 22.”

Transition:
“The key point is: use ss instead of guessing whether a port is listening.”

