39. Firewalld Practical Checks

“For firewalld, I like to separate checking from changing.

First check the service, state, active zones, services, and ports. Then, if a change is needed, test temporary first. Only make it permanent after validation.”

Demo line:
“I’ll run firewall-cmd --state, --get-active-zones, and --list-all. For adding services, I’ll show the commands with echo so we do not change the lab state.”

Transition:
“The professional habit here is temporary first, permanent after validation.”

