40. SELinux Quick Checks

“SELinux is very RHEL-relevant.

The important message is: do not immediately disable SELinux. Check the current mode, check labels, check processes, and look for AVC denials.”

Demo line:
“I’ll run getenforce and sestatus, then show labels with ls -Z. I’ll also show ausearch -m AVC -ts recent if available.”

Transition:
“Often the fix is a label or policy issue, not turning SELinux off.”

