41. Permissions Troubleshooting

“Sometimes the file permissions look fine, but access still fails because a parent directory blocks access.

That is where namei -l is really useful. It shows permissions for every part of the path.”

Demo line:
“I’ll run ls -l and stat on a demo file, then namei -l on the full path. This shows each directory in the path and its permissions.”

Transition:
“That makes it easier to spot when the problem is not the file itself, but one of the parent directories.”

